<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFFDFFE3E36700CDFA98FEDE" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFFDFFE3E36700CDFA98FEDE" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,862]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
[TL: ‘Palastina’ – generally accepted as environs of 
<collectingRegion id="9106F844FFFDFFE3E59B00CDFAB7FF72" box="[1185,1300,151,177]" country="Israel" name="Jerusalem" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">Jerusalem</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFFDFFE3E42400CCFAC1FF72" box="[1310,1378,150,177]" name="Israel" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">Israel</collectingCountry>
]; this taxon has been elevated fairly recently to specific status by 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFDFFE3E20C00E1FC5CFF16" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Bereczki, J. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Rota, J. &amp; Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N." box="[822,1023,187,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" pagination="749 - 757" refId="ref11329" refString="Toth, J. P., Bereczki, J., Varga, Z., Rota, J., Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N. (2014) Relationships within the Melitaea phoebe species group (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae): new insights from molecular and morphometric information. Systematic Entomology, 39, 749 - 757. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12083" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tóth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFDFFE3E24800E1FC07FF16" box="[882,932,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFDFFE3E53100E1FACEFF16" author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[1035,1389,187,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014)</bibRefCitation>
and confirmed recently by 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFDFFE3E0AC0085FDC2FF3A" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Verovnik, R. &amp; Wahlberg, N. &amp; Varadi, A. &amp; Bereczki, J." box="[406,609,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" pagination="267 - 281" refId="ref11547" refString="Toth, J. P., Varga, Z., Verovnik, R., Wahlberg, N., Varadi, A. &amp; Bereczki, J. (2017) Mito-nuclear discordance helps to reveal the phylogeographic patterns of Melitaea ornata (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae). Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 121, 267 - 281. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / biolinnean / blw 037" type="journal article" year="2017">
Tóth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFDFFE3E0E90085FDA7FF3A" box="[467,516,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
. There is considerable confusion between authors regarding Fruhstorfer’s 
<typeStatus id="8C798804FFFDFFE3E1AD0159FF64FEDE" box="[151,199,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
material; this is being actively investigated and the results will be published separately in due course.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
